iASF (ArchiSteamFarm) is a program that simulates game play to farm		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iSteam trading cards. Since it can simulate game play, it can naturally		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ialso simulate playing "Greedy Moon" - achieving the effect shown below		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iwithout any local configuration:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iTo implement this effect, modify the ASF configuration on your host		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
imachine running ASF. Open `config/[BotName].json` and modify these		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ithree parameters:		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- The first parameter sets the displayed name while farming cards.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- The second parameter sets the name shown after completing card		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifarming.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i- The third parameter controls "offline farming" (not showing online		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
istatus while farming). This must be disabled (false), otherwise		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ifriends won't see your status.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iAfter making these changes, restart ASF to activate the Greedy Moon		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ieffect.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
